<item>
            <title>[LU-19514] When kallsyms_lookup_name() is unavailable fallback to alternatives</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19514</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Breaking Lustre because of missing kallsyms_lookup_name() isn&apos;t really workable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There needs to be suitable alternatives for:&lt;br/&gt;
    alloc_workqueue_attrs() / alloc_workqueue_attrs() ... nice but not critical&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;vfree_atomic() &amp;#8211; not needed from v4.10? vfree will call vfree_atomic() when in_interrupt() is true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately we have no way to detect this via configure (aside from guessing based on kernel version).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So just copy the kernel implementation into Luster instead?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
