                            <comment id="476151" author="stancheff" created="Sat, 25 Oct 2025 01:31:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Config reports some KALLSYMS support and /proc/kallsyms is available .... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[shaun@alma9 ~]$ grep CONFIG_KALLSYMS /boot/config-6.17.1-1.ldiskfs.el9.x86_64 
CONFIG_KALLSYMS=y
# CONFIG_KALLSYMS_SELFTEST is not set
CONFIG_KALLSYMS_ALL=y
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will have to trace into the kprobe / kallsyms init code to know more..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="476059" author="simmonsja" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2025 13:34:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So you are running a kernel without CONFIG_KALLSYMS.&#160; We will really need some way of exporting symbols in the future. I think a kprobe solution is needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="475928" author="stancheff" created="Thu, 23 Oct 2025 15:45:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Kernel 6.17.2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[shaun@alma9 ~]$ sudo grep -w kallsyms_lookup_name /proc/kallsyms
ffffffff9c1dd830 T kallsyms_lookup_name
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some config&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[shaun@alma9 ~]$ grep KPROBE /boot/config-6.17.1-1.ldiskfs.el9.x86_64 
CONFIG_KPROBES=y
CONFIG_KPROBES_ON_FTRACE=y
CONFIG_HAVE_KPROBES=y
CONFIG_HAVE_KPROBES_ON_FTRACE=y
CONFIG_KPROBE_EVENTS=y
# CONFIG_KPROBE_EVENTS_ON_NOTRACE is not set
# CONFIG_BPF_KPROBE_OVERRIDE is not set
# CONFIG_KPROBE_EVENT_GEN_TEST is not set
# CONFIG_KPROBES_SANITY_TEST is not set
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="475876" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 23 Oct 2025 11:38:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is your setup that is causing this? Maybe instead of using kallysyms_lookup_name() maybe use kprobe directly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
